","timestamp":1766426864269,"ranges":[],"type":"recent_file"},{"mode":"Write","plan_file_path":"C:\Users\Saba\.firebender\projects\D:-AndroidProjects-EventApplication\plans\plan-f215fe.md","ranges":[],"type":"query_metadata"}]},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"From the new build error in the console output, I can see a different issue than what I was fixing before. This time it's a Dagger/Hilt dependency injection error:

```
error: [Dagger/DuplicateBindings] com.example.eventapplication.domain.repository.EventDetailsRepository is bound multiple times:
 @Binds @Singleton com.example.eventapplication.domain.repository.EventDetailsRepository com.example.eventapplication.di.DataModule.bindEventDetailsRepository(com.example.eventapplication.data.repository.EventDetailsRepositoryImpl)
 @Binds @Singleton com.example.eventapplication.domain.repository.EventDetailsRepository com.example.eventapplication.di.MockRepositoryModule.bindEventDetailsRepository(com.example.eventapplication.data.repository.MockEventDetailsRepository)
```

This is a common issue with Dagger/Hilt when we have multiple bindings for the same interface. The error is happening because:

1. In `DataModule`, there's a binding that provides `EventDetailsRepositoryImpl` as an implementation of `EventDetailsRepository`
2. In `MockRepositoryModule` (which we presumably created for testing), there's another binding that provides `MockEventDetailsRepository` as an implementation of the same `EventDetailsRepository`
3. Dagger doesn't know which one to use since both are marked with `@Binds` and `@Singleton`

To fix this, we need to make these modules mutually exclusive so that only one provides the binding at a time. This is typically done with:

