When you're done with your current set of changes to this file, you should call the read_lints tool with the specific file path and fix any newly introduced errors."},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I've fixed the issue with the search text appearing inside the icon. The problem was that the hint text was set on the TextInputLayout instead of the TextInputEditText.

### What was happening:

1. When the hint was set on the TextInputLayout (`android:hint="@string/browse_search_hint"`), the hint text was positioned relative to the TextInputLayout, which includes the area where the startIcon appears.

2. This caused the hint text "Search events..." to overlap with the search icon, making it look like the text was inside the icon.

### How I fixed it:

1. I removed the hint attribute from the TextInputLayout:
 ```xml
 <!-- Removed this line -->
 android:hint="@string/browse_search_hint"
 ```

2. I added the hint directly to the TextInputEditText instead:
 ```xml
 <com.google.android.material.textfield.TextInputEditText
 android:id="@+id/etSearch"
 android:layout_width="match_parent"
 android:layout_height="wrap_content"
 android:hint="@string/browse_search_hint"
 android:inputType="text"
 android:imeOptions="actionSearch"
 android:maxLines="1" />
 ```

This change ensures that the hint text appears in the proper position within the input field itself, not overlapping with the search icon. When a user clicks on the search field, the hint will properly animate up and out of the way, and the search icon will remain visible at the start of the field.

This follows Material Design best practices for search fields with icons."}]}]},"920d5eca-89e6-45c3-b281-2fe1b82fe2da":{"id":"920d5eca-89e6-45c3-b281-2fe1b82fe2da","name":"Clarifying the need for the /auth/me endpoint","timestamp":1766579865258,"messages":[{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"there's no api/auth/me on the backend api, what do we need this for?"}],"context":[{"file_path":"app/src/main/java/com/example/eventapplication/data/remote/api/UserApiService.kt","code_text":"package com.example.eventapplication.data.remote.api

